ZH: 我们可以用想象的力量创造美好的未来。
EN: We can use the power of imagination to create a better future.

ZH: 想象是人类独有的能力之一。
EN: Imagination is one of the unique abilities of human beings.

ZH: 孩子们常常会用想象力来玩耍。
EN: Children often use their imagination to play.

ZH: 我想象着在世界各地旅行的场景。
EN: I imagine scenes of traveling around the world.

ZH: 想象可以让我们逃离现实的困难。
EN: Imagination can help us escape the difficulties of reality.

ZH: 我总是尽量将我的梦想转化为现实，而不止于想象。
EN: I always try to turn my dreams into reality, not just imagine them.

ZH: 他能够通过想象力创造出极具创意的作品。
EN: He is able to create highly creative works through his imagination.

ZH: 想象力可以推动人们做出非凡的成就。
EN: Imagination can drive people to make extraordinary achievements.

ZH: 在创作中发挥想象力是非常重要的。
EN: It is very important to use imagination in creativity.

ZH: 想象可以让我们看到世界的不同角度。
EN: Imagination can allow us to see the world from different perspectives.

ZH: 我在写小说时常常会用到大量的想象。
EN: I often use a lot of imagination when writing novels.

ZH: 想象是解决问题的第一步。
EN: Imagination is the first step in solving problems.

ZH: 学习一门新的语言需要很多的想象力。
EN: Learning a new language requires a lot of imagination.

ZH: 她总是充满了创意和想象力。
EN: She is always full of creativity and imagination.

ZH: 想象可以激发潜在的创造力。
EN: Imagination can inspire latent creativity.

ZH: 我们要教育孩子如何善于运用想象力。
EN: We should educate children on how to use their imagination effectively.

ZH: 想象是人们创作作品时的基础。
EN: Imagination is the foundation for people to create works.

ZH: 对于艺术家来说，想象力是至关重要的。
EN: Imagination is crucial for artists.

ZH: 做梦是一种无意识下的想象活动。
EN: Dreaming is a form of unconscious imaginative activity.

ZH: 想象力可以带来无穷无尽的可能性。
EN: Imagination can bring endless possibilities.
